critique: This executive order pertains to land use in Alaska in 1934. It withdraws one lot from settlement for the War Department and revokes a previous order regarding another lot. Given the limited scope and specific nature of the order, it's difficult to assign strong ideological biases. It's primarily an administrative action related to federal land management and military use. There is no clear indication of stances on immigration, executive power, federalism, national security vs. civil liberties, economic regulation, or social inclusion. Therefore, most scores will be neutral.
